The paper focuses on identifying essential sentences in Stack Overflow answers to help users navigate the platform. This involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of user experience and usability in navigating Stack Overflow, which falls under the sub-categories of Software Engineering (cs.SE), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), and Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
